{
  "video_id": "cWC_zDdF74s",
  "title": "Tristram Stuart: The global food waste scandal",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 16219.000000000002,
      "text": "Translator: Joseph Geni Reviewer: Morton Bast"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16219.000000000002,
      "end_time": 18977.0,
      "text": "The job of uncovering the global food waste scandal"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18977.0,
      "end_time": 21995.0,
      "text": "started for me when I was 15 years old."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21995.0,
      "end_time": 24516.0,
      "text": "I bought some pigs. I was living in Sussex."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24516.0,
      "end_time": 26899.0,
      "text": "And I started to feed them in the most traditional"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26899.0,
      "end_time": 28870.0,
      "text": "and environmentally friendly way."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 28870.0,
      "end_time": 31195.0,
      "text": "I went to my school kitchen, and I said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 31195.0,
      "end_time": 32741.0,
      "text": "\"Give me the scraps that my school friends have turned"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 32741.0,
      "end_time": 33607.0,
      "text": "their noses up at.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 33607.0,
      "end_time": 36271.0,
      "text": "I went to the local baker and took their stale bread."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 36271.0,
      "end_time": 39003.0,
      "text": "I went to the local greengrocer, and I went to a farmer"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39003.0,
      "end_time": 40841.0,
      "text": "who was throwing away potatoes because they were"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 40841.0,
      "end_time": 44027.0,
      "text": "the wrong shape or size for supermarkets."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 44027.0,
      "end_time": 47116.0,
      "text": "This was great. My pigs turned that food waste"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 47116.0,
      "end_time": 49773.0,
      "text": "into delicious pork. I sold that pork"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 49773.0,
      "end_time": 51760.0,
      "text": "to my school friends' parents, and I made"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 51760.0,
      "end_time": 56397.0,
      "text": "a good pocket money addition to my teenage allowance."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 56397.0,
      "end_time": 59279.0,
      "text": "But I noticed that most of the food that I was giving my pigs"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 59279.0,
      "end_time": 61662.0,
      "text": "was in fact fit for human consumption,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 61662.0,
      "end_time": 63931.0,
      "text": "and that I was only scratching the surface,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 63931.0,
      "end_time": 66793.0,
      "text": "and that right the way up the food supply chain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 66793.0,
      "end_time": 70011.0,
      "text": "in supermarkets, greengrocers, bakers, in our homes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 70011.0,
      "end_time": 73271.0,
      "text": "in factories and farms, we were hemorrhaging out food."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 73271.0,
      "end_time": 75868.0,
      "text": "Supermarkets didn't even want to talk to me"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 75868.0,
      "end_time": 77242.0,
      "text": "about how much food they were wasting."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 77242.0,
      "end_time": 79726.0,
      "text": "I'd been round the back. I'd seen bins full of food"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 79726.0,
      "end_time": 82477.0,
      "text": "being locked and then trucked off to landfill sites,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 82477.0,
      "end_time": 85498.0,
      "text": "and I thought, surely there is something more sensible"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 85498.0,
      "end_time": 88665.0,
      "text": "to do with food than waste it."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 88665.0,
      "end_time": 90970.0,
      "text": "One morning, when I was feeding my pigs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 90970.0,
      "end_time": 94657.0,
      "text": "I noticed a particularly tasty-looking sun-dried tomato loaf"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 94657.0,
      "end_time": 96732.0,
      "text": "that used to crop up from time to time."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 96732.0,
      "end_time": 98134.0,
      "text": "I grabbed hold of it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 98134.0,
      "end_time": 101680.0,
      "text": "sat down, and ate my breakfast with my pigs. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 101680.0,
      "end_time": 104800.0,
      "text": "That was the first act of what I later learned to call freeganism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 104800.0,
      "end_time": 109055.0,
      "text": "really an exhibition of the injustice of food waste,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 109055.0,
      "end_time": 111405.0,
      "text": "and the provision of the solution to food waste,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 111405.0,
      "end_time": 114059.0,
      "text": "which is simply to sit down and eat food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 114059.0,
      "end_time": 115547.0,
      "text": "rather than throwing it away."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 115547.0,
      "end_time": 118826.0,
      "text": "That became, as it were, a way of confronting"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 118826.0,
      "end_time": 121813.0,
      "text": "large businesses in the business of wasting food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 121813.0,
      "end_time": 124334.0,
      "text": "and exposing, most importantly, to the public,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 124334.0,
      "end_time": 126504.0,
      "text": "that when we're talking about food being thrown away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 126504.0,
      "end_time": 128643.0,
      "text": "we're not talking about rotten stuff, we're not talking about"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 128643.0,
      "end_time": 131355.0,
      "text": "stuff that's beyond the pale."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 131355.0,
      "end_time": 133471.0,
      "text": "We're talking about good, fresh food that is being wasted"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 133471.0,
      "end_time": 136009.0,
      "text": "on a colossal scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 136009.0,
      "end_time": 137866.0,
      "text": "Eventually, I set about writing my book,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 137866.0,
      "end_time": 139920.0,
      "text": "really to demonstrate the extent of this problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 139920.0,
      "end_time": 143316.0,
      "text": "on a global scale. What this shows is"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 143316.0,
      "end_time": 146795.0,
      "text": "a nation-by-nation breakdown of the likely level"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 146795.0,
      "end_time": 149897.0,
      "text": "of food waste in each country in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 149897.0,
      "end_time": 153785.0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, empirical data, good, hard stats, don't exist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 153785.0,
      "end_time": 156267.0,
      "text": "and therefore to prove my point, I first of all had to find"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 156267.0,
      "end_time": 158420.0,
      "text": "some proxy way of uncovering"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 158420.0,
      "end_time": 160665.0,
      "text": "how much food was being wasted."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 160665.0,
      "end_time": 163221.0,
      "text": "So I took the food supply of every single country"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 163221.0,
      "end_time": 166263.0,
      "text": "and I compared it to what was actually likely"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 166263.0,
      "end_time": 168295.0,
      "text": "to be being consumed in each country."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 168295.0,
      "end_time": 172182.0,
      "text": "That's based on diet intake surveys, it's based on"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 172182.0,
      "end_time": 174848.0,
      "text": "levels of obesity, it's based on a range of factors"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 174848.0,
      "end_time": 176190.0,
      "text": "that gives you an approximate guess"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 176190.0,
      "end_time": 179417.0,
      "text": "as to how much food is actually going into people's mouths."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 179417.0,
      "end_time": 182146.0,
      "text": "That black line in the middle of that table"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 182146.0,
      "end_time": 185142.0,
      "text": "is the likely level of consumption"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 185142.0,
      "end_time": 189504.0,
      "text": "with an allowance for certain levels of inevitable waste."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 189504.0,
      "end_time": 191423.0,
      "text": "There will always be waste. I'm not that unrealistic"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 191423.0,
      "end_time": 193403.0,
      "text": "that I think we can live in a waste-free world."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 193403.0,
      "end_time": 197276.0,
      "text": "But that black line shows what a food supply should be"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 197276.0,
      "end_time": 201730.0,
      "text": "in a country if they allow for a good, stable, secure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 201730.0,
      "end_time": 205479.0,
      "text": "nutritional diet for every person in that country."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 205479.0,
      "end_time": 207886.0,
      "text": "Any dot above that line, and you'll quickly notice that"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 207886.0,
      "end_time": 210587.0,
      "text": "that includes most countries in the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 210587.0,
      "end_time": 214876.0,
      "text": "represents unnecessary surplus, and is likely to reflect"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 214876.0,
      "end_time": 217498.0,
      "text": "levels of waste in each country."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 217498.0,
      "end_time": 220767.0,
      "text": "As a country gets richer, it invests more and more"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 220767.0,
      "end_time": 222058.0,
      "text": "in getting more and more surplus"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 222058.0,
      "end_time": 224868.0,
      "text": "into its shops and restaurants,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 224868.0,
      "end_time": 226924.0,
      "text": "and as you can see, most European"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 226924.0,
      "end_time": 228336.0,
      "text": "and North American countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 228336.0,
      "end_time": 231476.0,
      "text": "fall between 150 and 200 percent"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 231476.0,
      "end_time": 234856.0,
      "text": "of the nutritional requirements of their populations."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 234856.0,
      "end_time": 237264.0,
      "text": "So a country like America has twice as much food"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 237264.0,
      "end_time": 239868.0,
      "text": "on its shop shelves and in its restaurants"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 239868.0,
      "end_time": 243436.0,
      "text": "than is actually required to feed the American people."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 243436.0,
      "end_time": 244996.0,
      "text": "But the thing that really struck me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 244996.0,
      "end_time": 249211.0,
      "text": "when I plotted all this data, and it was a lot of numbers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 249211.0,
      "end_time": 252877.0,
      "text": "was that you can see how it levels off."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 252877.0,
      "end_time": 255945.0,
      "text": "Countries rapidly shoot towards that 150 mark,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 255945.0,
      "end_time": 259233.0,
      "text": "and then they level off, and they don't really go on rising"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 259233.0,
      "end_time": 260779.0,
      "text": "as you might expect."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 260779.0,
      "end_time": 263324.0,
      "text": "So I decided to unpack that data a little bit further"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 263324.0,
      "end_time": 265609.0,
      "text": "to see if that was true or false."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 265609.0,
      "end_time": 267103.0,
      "text": "And that's what I came up with."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 267103.0,
      "end_time": 269030.0,
      "text": "If you include not just the food that ends up"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 269030.0,
      "end_time": 271154.0,
      "text": "in shops and restaurants, but also the food"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 271154.0,
      "end_time": 273310.0,
      "text": "that people feed to livestock,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 273310.0,
      "end_time": 276813.0,
      "text": "the maize, the soy, the wheat, that humans could eat"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 276813.0,
      "end_time": 279294.0,
      "text": "but choose to fatten livestock instead to produce"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 279294.0,
      "end_time": 281225.0,
      "text": "increasing amounts of meat and dairy products,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 281225.0,
      "end_time": 282892.0,
      "text": "what you find is that most rich countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 282892.0,
      "end_time": 287215.0,
      "text": "have between three and four times the amount of food"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 287215.0,
      "end_time": 290299.0,
      "text": "that their population needs to feed itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 290299.0,
      "end_time": 293582.0,
      "text": "A country like America has four times the amount of food"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 293582.0,
      "end_time": 296544.0,
      "text": "that it needs."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 296544.0,
      "end_time": 299506.0,
      "text": "When people talk about the need to increase global"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 299506.0,
      "end_time": 302166.0,
      "text": "food production to feed those nine billion people"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 302166.0,
      "end_time": 304678.0,
      "text": "that are expected on the planet by 2050,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 304678.0,
      "end_time": 306399.0,
      "text": "I always think of these graphs."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 306399.0,
      "end_time": 309350.0,
      "text": "The fact is, we have an enormous buffer"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 309350.0,
      "end_time": 313231.0,
      "text": "in rich countries between ourselves and hunger."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 313231.0,
      "end_time": 317907.0,
      "text": "We've never had such gargantuan surpluses before."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 317907.0,
      "end_time": 320573.0,
      "text": "In many ways, this is a great success story"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 320573.0,
      "end_time": 324712.0,
      "text": "of human civilization, of the agricultural surpluses"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 324712.0,
      "end_time": 328065.0,
      "text": "that we set out to achieve 12,000 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 328065.0,
      "end_time": 331622.0,
      "text": "It is a success story. It has been a success story."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 331622.0,
      "end_time": 334159.0,
      "text": "But what we have to recognize now is that we are"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 334159.0,
      "end_time": 337791.0,
      "text": "reaching the ecological limits that our planet can bear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 337791.0,
      "end_time": 340428.0,
      "text": "and when we chop down forests, as we are every day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 340428.0,
      "end_time": 341776.0,
      "text": "to grow more and more food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 341776.0,
      "end_time": 345524.0,
      "text": "when we extract water from depleting water reserves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 345524.0,
      "end_time": 348912.0,
      "text": "when we emit fossil fuel emissions in the quest"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 348912.0,
      "end_time": 350204.0,
      "text": "to grow more and more food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 350204.0,
      "end_time": 353055.0,
      "text": "and then we throw away so much of it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 353055.0,
      "end_time": 355991.0,
      "text": "we have to think about what we can start saving."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 355991.0,
      "end_time": 359716.0,
      "text": "And yesterday, I went to one of the local supermarkets"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 359716.0,
      "end_time": 361932.0,
      "text": "that I often visit to"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 361932.0,
      "end_time": 366113.0,
      "text": "inspect, if you like, what they're throwing away."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 366113.0,
      "end_time": 368516.0,
      "text": "I found quite a few packets of biscuits amongst"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 368516.0,
      "end_time": 370143.0,
      "text": "all the fruit and vegetables and everything else"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 370143.0,
      "end_time": 371090.0,
      "text": "that was in there."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 371090.0,
      "end_time": 373530.0,
      "text": "And I thought, well this could serve as a symbol for today."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 373530.0,
      "end_time": 375965.0,
      "text": "So I want you to imagine that these nine biscuits"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 375965.0,
      "end_time": 379493.0,
      "text": "that I found in the bin represent the global food supply,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 379493.0,
      "end_time": 381094.0,
      "text": "okay? We start out with nine."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 381094.0,
      "end_time": 384577.0,
      "text": "That's what's in fields around the world every single year."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 384577.0,
      "end_time": 386338.0,
      "text": "The first biscuit we're going to lose"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 386338.0,
      "end_time": 388097.0,
      "text": "before we even leave the farm."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 388097.0,
      "end_time": 391362.0,
      "text": "That's a problem primarily associated with"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 391362.0,
      "end_time": 393026.0,
      "text": "developing work agriculture, whether it's"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 393026.0,
      "end_time": 395531.0,
      "text": "a lack of infrastructure, refrigeration, pasteurization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 395531.0,
      "end_time": 398444.0,
      "text": "grain stores, even basic fruit crates, which means"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 398444.0,
      "end_time": 402193.0,
      "text": "that food goes to waste before it even leaves the fields."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 402193.0,
      "end_time": 405689.0,
      "text": "The next three biscuits are the foods that we decide"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 405689.0,
      "end_time": 409429.0,
      "text": "to feed to livestock, the maize, the wheat and the soya."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 409429.0,
      "end_time": 414273.0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, our beasts are inefficient animals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 414273.0,
      "end_time": 418448.0,
      "text": "and they turn two-thirds of that into feces and heat,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 418448.0,
      "end_time": 421066.0,
      "text": "so we've lost those two, and we've only kept this one"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 421066.0,
      "end_time": 423300.0,
      "text": "in meat and dairy products."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 423300.0,
      "end_time": 426884.0,
      "text": "Two more we're going to throw away directly into bins."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 426884.0,
      "end_time": 428437.0,
      "text": "This is what most of us think of when we think"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 428437.0,
      "end_time": 430948.0,
      "text": "of food waste, what ends up in the garbage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 430948.0,
      "end_time": 432796.0,
      "text": "what ends up in supermarket bins,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 432796.0,
      "end_time": 435526.0,
      "text": "what ends up in restaurant bins. We've lost another two,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 435526.0,
      "end_time": 439284.0,
      "text": "and we've left ourselves with just four biscuits to feed on."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 439284.0,
      "end_time": 443083.0,
      "text": "That is not a superlatively efficient use of global resources,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 443083.0,
      "end_time": 445543.0,
      "text": "especially when you think of the billion hungry people"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 445543.0,
      "end_time": 447683.0,
      "text": "that exist already in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 447683.0,
      "end_time": 449666.0,
      "text": "Having gone through the data, I then needed"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 449666.0,
      "end_time": 453344.0,
      "text": "to demonstrate where that food ends up."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 453344.0,
      "end_time": 454963.0,
      "text": "Where does it end up? We're used to seeing the stuff"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 454963.0,
      "end_time": 456866.0,
      "text": "on our plates, but what about all the stuff"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 456866.0,
      "end_time": 458806.0,
      "text": "that goes missing in between?"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 458806.0,
      "end_time": 461218.0,
      "text": "Supermarkets are an easy place to start."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 461218.0,
      "end_time": 463809.0,
      "text": "This is the result of my hobby,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 463809.0,
      "end_time": 468285.0,
      "text": "which is unofficial bin inspections. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 468285.0,
      "end_time": 470882.0,
      "text": "Strange you might think, but if we could rely on corporations"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 470882.0,
      "end_time": 473990.0,
      "text": "to tell us what they were doing in the back of their stores,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 473990.0,
      "end_time": 476474.0,
      "text": "we wouldn't need to go sneaking around the back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 476474.0,
      "end_time": 479030.0,
      "text": "opening up bins and having a look at what's inside."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 479030.0,
      "end_time": 480990.0,
      "text": "But this is what you can see more or less on"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 480990.0,
      "end_time": 484502.0,
      "text": "every street corner in Britain, in Europe, in North America."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 484502.0,
      "end_time": 487568.0,
      "text": "It represents a colossal waste of food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 487568.0,
      "end_time": 490070.0,
      "text": "but what I discovered whilst I was writing my book"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 490070.0,
      "end_time": 493414.0,
      "text": "was that this very evident abundance of waste"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 493414.0,
      "end_time": 496358.0,
      "text": "was actually the tip of the iceberg."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 496358.0,
      "end_time": 498414.0,
      "text": "When you start going up the supply chain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 498414.0,
      "end_time": 501400.0,
      "text": "you find where the real food waste is happening"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 501400.0,
      "end_time": 503387.0,
      "text": "on a gargantuan scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 503387.0,
      "end_time": 504860.0,
      "text": "Can I have a show of hands"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 504860.0,
      "end_time": 509318.0,
      "text": "if you have a loaf of sliced bread in your house?"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 509318.0,
      "end_time": 511237.0,
      "text": "Who lives in a household where that crust --"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 511237.0,
      "end_time": 514430.0,
      "text": "that slice at the first and last end of each loaf --"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 514429.99999999994,
      "end_time": 516873.99999999994,
      "text": "who lives in a household where it does get eaten?"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 516874.0,
      "end_time": 519241.0,
      "text": "Okay, most people, not everyone, but most people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 519241.0,
      "end_time": 521697.0,
      "text": "and this is, I'm glad to say, what I see across the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 521697.0,
      "end_time": 524486.0,
      "text": "and yet has anyone seen a supermarket or sandwich shop"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 524486.0,
      "end_time": 526722.0,
      "text": "anywhere in the world that serves sandwiches"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 526722.0,
      "end_time": 528496.0,
      "text": "with crusts on it? (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 528496.0,
      "end_time": 530079.0,
      "text": "I certainly haven't."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 530079.0,
      "end_time": 535247.0,
      "text": "So I kept on thinking, where do those crusts go? (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 535247.0,
      "end_time": 537462.0,
      "text": "This is the answer, unfortunately:"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 537462.0,
      "end_time": 539374.0,
      "text": "13,000 slices of fresh bread coming out of"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 539374.0,
      "end_time": 544975.0,
      "text": "this one single factory every single day, day-fresh bread."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 544975.0,
      "end_time": 546484.0,
      "text": "In the same year that I visited this factory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 546484.0,
      "end_time": 550934.0,
      "text": "I went to Pakistan, where people in 2008 were going hungry"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 550934.0,
      "end_time": 554711.0,
      "text": "as a result of a squeeze on global food supplies."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 554711.0,
      "end_time": 556895.0,
      "text": "We contribute to that squeeze"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 556895.0,
      "end_time": 559887.0,
      "text": "by depositing food in bins here in Britain"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 559887.0,
      "end_time": 562094.0,
      "text": "and elsewhere in the world. We take food"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 562094.0,
      "end_time": 565200.0,
      "text": "off the market shelves that hungry people depend on."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 565200.0,
      "end_time": 567750.0,
      "text": "Go one step up, and you get to farmers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 567750.0,
      "end_time": 569910.0,
      "text": "who throw away sometimes a third or even more"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 569910.0,
      "end_time": 571955.0,
      "text": "of their harvest because of cosmetic standards."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 571955.0,
      "end_time": 574878.0,
      "text": "This farmer, for example, has invested 16,000 pounds"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 574878.0,
      "end_time": 578302.0,
      "text": "in growing spinach, not one leaf of which he harvested,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 578302.0,
      "end_time": 580756.0,
      "text": "because there was a little bit of grass growing in amongst it."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 580756.0,
      "end_time": 583236.0,
      "text": "Potatoes that are cosmetically imperfect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 583236.0,
      "end_time": 584769.0,
      "text": "all going for pigs."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 584769.0,
      "end_time": 588807.0,
      "text": "Parsnips that are too small for supermarket specifications,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 588807.0,
      "end_time": 590823.0,
      "text": "tomatoes in Tenerife,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 590823.0,
      "end_time": 592628.0,
      "text": "oranges in Florida,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 592628.0,
      "end_time": 595632.0,
      "text": "bananas in Ecuador, where I visited last year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 595632.0,
      "end_time": 598047.0,
      "text": "all being discarded. This is one day's waste"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 598047.0,
      "end_time": 600584.0,
      "text": "from one banana plantation in Ecuador."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 600584.0,
      "end_time": 602792.0,
      "text": "All being discarded, perfectly edible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 602792.0,
      "end_time": 605280.0,
      "text": "because they're the wrong shape or size."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 605280.0,
      "end_time": 606860.0,
      "text": "If we do that to fruit and vegetables,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 606860.0,
      "end_time": 609675.0,
      "text": "you bet we can do it to animals too."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 609675.0,
      "end_time": 612414.0,
      "text": "Liver, lungs, heads, tails,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 612414.0,
      "end_time": 614392.0,
      "text": "kidneys, testicles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 614392.0,
      "end_time": 616105.0,
      "text": "all of these things which are traditional,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 616105.0,
      "end_time": 618920.0,
      "text": "delicious and nutritious parts of our gastronomy"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 618920.0,
      "end_time": 622416.0,
      "text": "go to waste. Offal consumption has halved"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 622416.0,
      "end_time": 624951.0,
      "text": "in Britain and America in the last 30 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 624951.0,
      "end_time": 627591.0,
      "text": "As a result, this stuff gets fed to dogs at best,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 627591.0,
      "end_time": 629360.0,
      "text": "or is incinerated."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 629360.0,
      "end_time": 633207.0,
      "text": "This man, in Kashgar, Xinjiang province, in Western China,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 633207.0,
      "end_time": 635122.0,
      "text": "is serving up his national dish."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 635122.0,
      "end_time": 636837.0,
      "text": "It's called sheep's organs."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 636837.0,
      "end_time": 638504.0,
      "text": "It's delicious, it's nutritious,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 638504.0,
      "end_time": 640912.0,
      "text": "and as I learned when I went to Kashgar,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 640912.0,
      "end_time": 643981.0,
      "text": "it symbolizes their taboo against food waste."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 643981.0,
      "end_time": 646177.0,
      "text": "I was sitting in a roadside cafe."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 646177.0,
      "end_time": 648781.0,
      "text": "A chef came to talk to me, I finished my bowl,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 648781.0,
      "end_time": 650546.0,
      "text": "and halfway through the conversation, he stopped talking"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 650546.0,
      "end_time": 653112.0,
      "text": "and he started frowning into my bowl."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 653112.0,
      "end_time": 654991.0,
      "text": "I thought, \"My goodness, what taboo have I broken?"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 654991.0,
      "end_time": 656585.0,
      "text": "How have I insulted my host?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 656585.0,
      "end_time": 658323.0,
      "text": "He pointed at three grains of rice"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 658323.0,
      "end_time": 662607.0,
      "text": "at the bottom of my bowl, and he said, \"Clean.\" (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 662607.0,
      "end_time": 664519.0,
      "text": "I thought, \"My God, you know, I go around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 664519.0,
      "end_time": 665935.0,
      "text": "telling people to stop wasting food."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 665935.0,
      "end_time": 670984.0,
      "text": "This guy has thrashed me at my own game.\" (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 670984.0,
      "end_time": 674207.0,
      "text": "But it gave me faith. It gave me faith that we, the people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 674207.0,
      "end_time": 679243.0,
      "text": "do have the power to stop this tragic waste of resources"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 679243.0,
      "end_time": 681443.0,
      "text": "if we regard it as socially unacceptable"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 681443.0,
      "end_time": 682947.0,
      "text": "to waste food on a colossal scale,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 682947.0,
      "end_time": 685515.0,
      "text": "if we make noise about it, tell corporations about it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 685515.0,
      "end_time": 688135.0,
      "text": "tell governments we want to see an end to food waste,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 688135.0,
      "end_time": 690631.0,
      "text": "we do have the power to bring about that change."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 690631.0,
      "end_time": 693343.0,
      "text": "Fish, 40 to 60 percent of European fish"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 693343.0,
      "end_time": 696424.0,
      "text": "are discarded at sea, they don't even get landed."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 696424.0,
      "end_time": 699116.0,
      "text": "In our homes, we've lost touch with food."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 699116.0,
      "end_time": 702033.0,
      "text": "This is an experiment I did on three lettuces."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 702033.0,
      "end_time": 704671.0,
      "text": "Who keeps lettuces in their fridge?"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 704671.0,
      "end_time": 708247.0,
      "text": "Most people. The one on the left"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 708247.0,
      "end_time": 709700.0,
      "text": "was kept in a fridge for 10 days."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 709700.0,
      "end_time": 711919.0,
      "text": "The one in the middle, on my kitchen table. Not much difference."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 711919.0,
      "end_time": 714494.0,
      "text": "The one on the right I treated like cut flowers."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 714494.0,
      "end_time": 716676.0,
      "text": "It's a living organism, cut the slice off,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 716676.0,
      "end_time": 718119.0,
      "text": "stuck it in a vase of water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 718119.0,
      "end_time": 721667.0,
      "text": "it was all right for another two weeks after this."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 721667.0,
      "end_time": 723626.0,
      "text": "Some food waste, as I said at the beginning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 723626.0,
      "end_time": 725458.0,
      "text": "will inevitably arise, so the question is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 725458.0,
      "end_time": 727656.0,
      "text": "what is the best thing to do with it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 727656.0,
      "end_time": 729162.0,
      "text": "I answered that question when I was 15."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 729162.0,
      "end_time": 734572.0,
      "text": "In fact, humans answered that question 6,000 years ago:"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 734572.0,
      "end_time": 736784.0,
      "text": "We domesticated pigs"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 736784.0,
      "end_time": 739556.0,
      "text": "to turn food waste back into food."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 739556.0,
      "end_time": 743287.0,
      "text": "And yet, in Europe, that practice has become illegal"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 743287.0,
      "end_time": 746574.0,
      "text": "since 2001 as a result of the foot-and-mouth outbreak."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 746574.0,
      "end_time": 748475.0,
      "text": "It's unscientific. It's unnecessary."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 748475.0,
      "end_time": 751158.0,
      "text": "If you cook food for pigs, just as if"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 751158.0,
      "end_time": 754127.0,
      "text": "you cook food for humans, it is rendered safe."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 754127.0,
      "end_time": 756687.0,
      "text": "It's also a massive saving of resources."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 756687.0,
      "end_time": 759582.0,
      "text": "At the moment, Europe depends on importing"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 759582.0,
      "end_time": 761248.0,
      "text": "millions of tons of soy from South America,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 761248.0,
      "end_time": 764134.0,
      "text": "where its production contributes to global warming,"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 764134.0,
      "end_time": 766734.0,
      "text": "to deforestation, to biodiversity loss,"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 766734.0,
      "end_time": 769181.0,
      "text": "to feed livestock here in Europe."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 769181.0,
      "end_time": 771483.0,
      "text": "At the same time we throw away millions of tons"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 771483.0,
      "end_time": 774702.0,
      "text": "of food waste which we could and should be feeding them."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 774702.0,
      "end_time": 777564.0,
      "text": "If we did that, and fed it to pigs, we would save"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 777564.0,
      "end_time": 779915.0,
      "text": "that amount of carbon."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 779915.0,
      "end_time": 783007.0,
      "text": "If we feed our food waste which is the current"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 783007.0,
      "end_time": 785302.0,
      "text": "government favorite way of getting rid of food waste,"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 785302.0,
      "end_time": 788103.0,
      "text": "to anaerobic digestion, which turns food waste"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 788103.0,
      "end_time": 790407.0,
      "text": "into gas to produce electricity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 790407.0,
      "end_time": 794140.0,
      "text": "you save a paltry 448 kilograms of carbon dioxide"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 794140.0,
      "end_time": 796622.0,
      "text": "per ton of food waste. It's much better to feed it to pigs."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 796622.0,
      "end_time": 799882.0,
      "text": "We knew that during the war. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 799882.0,
      "end_time": 804156.0,
      "text": "A silver lining: It has kicked off globally,"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 804156.0,
      "end_time": 805926.0,
      "text": "the quest to tackle food waste."
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 805926.0,
      "end_time": 809780.0,
      "text": "Feeding the 5,000 is an event I first organized in 2009."
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 809780.0,
      "end_time": 812036.0,
      "text": "We fed 5,000 people all on food that otherwise"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 812036.0,
      "end_time": 813434.0,
      "text": "would have been wasted."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 813434.0,
      "end_time": 815734.0,
      "text": "Since then, it's happened again in London,"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 815734.0,
      "end_time": 817867.0,
      "text": "it's happening internationally, and across the country."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 817867.0,
      "end_time": 820210.0,
      "text": "It's a way of organizations coming together"
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 820210.0,
      "end_time": 823952.0,
      "text": "to celebrate food, to say the best thing to do with food"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 823952.0,
      "end_time": 826759.0,
      "text": "is to eat and enjoy it, and to stop wasting it."
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 826759.0,
      "end_time": 829352.0,
      "text": "For the sake of the planet we live on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 829352.0,
      "end_time": 832632.0,
      "text": "for the sake of our children,"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 832632.0,
      "end_time": 834202.0,
      "text": "for the sake of all the other"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 834202.0,
      "end_time": 836650.0,
      "text": "organisms that share our planet with us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 836650.0,
      "end_time": 839691.0,
      "text": "we are a terrestrial animal, and we depend on our land"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 839691.0,
      "end_time": 842313.0,
      "text": "for food. At the moment, we are trashing our land"
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 842313.0,
      "end_time": 844827.0,
      "text": "to grow food that no one eats."
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 844827.0,
      "end_time": 847923.0,
      "text": "Stop wasting food. Thank you very much. (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 847923.0,
      "end_time": 857923.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}